The paper discusses building a self-adaptive network security system using unconventional techniques such as fuzzy logic and biological inspired algorithms. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The use of self-adaptive techniques also suggests the paper may fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY) or software engineering (cs.SE).
